      <link>http://knowledge.cta.int/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Diversity-in-local-food-production-combats-obesity-in-the-Caribbean</link>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;In the Caribbean region, obesity as a result of growing consumption of imported processed foods is becoming a growing health problem. In response, the Farm to Fork project – a multi-sector, integrated approach to food and nutrition security– together with smallholder farmers in St Kitts-Nevis and Trinidad and Tobago, and in Guyana and St Lucia – has developed year-round production systems of fruit and vegetables in order to supply the national school feeding programmes, as a step towards improving children’s nutrition and dietary diversity. (IDRC, 13/05/2015)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
